<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
    <title>CONSTIPATION</title>
    <link href="Case_sheet_styles.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
    <link href="Case_sheet_styles_dark.css" id="dark-styles" rel="alternate stylesheet"
      title="dark">
    <script src="https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api"></script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode">🌙 Dark Mode</button>
    <div class="git General">
      <h3>1ST COMPLAINT: CONSTIPATION</h3>
      <!-- S: Site -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Site of Discomfort</span>
          <ul>
            <li>GENERALISED BLOATING/FULLNESS
              <ul>
                <li class="git">Slow-transit constipation</li>
                <li class="git">Irritable Bowel Syndrome (IBS-C)</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>RECTAL FULLNESS / PRESSURE / BLOCKAGE
              <ul>
                <li class="git ortho-specific">Obstructive defecation</li>
                <li class="git cns">Pelvic floor dyssynergia</li>
                <li class="git">Rectocele</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>LOWER ABDOMINAL CRAMPING PAIN
              <ul>
                <li class="git">IBS-C</li>
                <li class="git">Diverticular disease</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Can you describe the discomfort? Is it a general
          abdominal bloating, or a feeling of blockage lower down?"</span></div>
      <!-- O: Onset -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>: Onset</span>
          <ul>
            <li>ACUTE / RECENT (Days to weeks)
              <ul>
                <li class="git emergency">Bowel obstruction</li>
                <li class="cns surgery">Medication-induced (e.g., opioids,
                  anticholinergics)</li>
                <li class="General">Change in diet/activity, dehydration</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>CHRONIC (Months to years)
              <ul>
                <li class="git">Functional constipation / IBS-C</li>
                <li class="endocrine">Hypothyroidism</li>
                <li class="cns">Neurological disorders (Parkinson's, MS)</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>Trigger</p>
              <ul>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"When did this constipation begin? Has it been
          lifelong, or is this a recent change?"</span></div>
      <!-- D: Duration & Frequency -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>: Duration &amp; Frequency</span>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"On average, how many days do you go between bowel
          movements?"</span></div>
      <!-- A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>: Aggravating &amp;
            Relieving Factors</span>
          <ul>
            <li>AGGRAVATING
              <ul>
                <li class="General">Low fiber , low fluid , inactivity</li>
                <li class="cns">Stress</li>
                <li class="git">Certain foods (e.g., dairy, processed foods)</li>
                <li class="General">Medication (e.g., opioids, anticholinergics)</li>
                <li class="General">Pain in back passage</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>RELIEVING
              <ul>
                <li class="General">Exercise, increased fluids, fiber</li>
                <li class="git">Laxatives (ask which type and frequency)</li>
                <li class="General">Specific foods (prunes, coffee)</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"What seems to make it worse? What have you tried
          that helps?"</span></div>
      <!-- C: Character of Stool -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>: Character</span>
          <ul>
            <li>STOOL FORM (Bristol Stool Chart)
              <ul>
                <li class="git">Type 1 (separate hard lumps)</li>
                <li class="git">Type 2 (lumpy, sausage-shaped)</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>blood in stool</li>
            <li>diarrhoea</li>
            <li>wind</li>
            <li>STRAINING / DIFFICULTY
              <ul>
                <li class="git cns">Pelvic floor dyssynergia</li>
                <li class="git">Obstructive defecation</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>SENSE OF INCOMPLETE EVACUATION
              <ul>
                <li class="git cns">Functional constipation</li>
                <li class="git">Rectal prolapse</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"What do your stools typically look like? Are they
          hard, small pellets? Do you have to strain excessively?"</span></div>
      <!-- R: Radiation -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Radiation</span>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Do you get any pain that seems to spread from your
          abdomen?"</span></div>
      <!-- A: Associated Symptoms -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>: Associated Symptoms</span>
          <ul>
            <li>ABDOMINAL PAIN/BLOATING
              <ul>
                <li class="git">IBS-C</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>NAUSEA / VOMITING
              <ul>
                <li class="git emergency">Bowel obstruction</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>CRAMPS - muscle</li>
            <ul>
              <li>hypocalcemia</li>
            </ul>
            <li>BLOOD IN STOOL (Hematochezia)
              <ul>
                <li class="oncology git">Colorectal cancer</li>
                <li class="git">Diverticulosis, hemorrhoids, fissures</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>UNEXPLAINED WEIGHT LOSS
              <ul>
                <li class="oncology">Malignancy</li>
                <li class="endocrine">Hyperthyroidism (less common)</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>FATIGUE, COLD INTOLERANCE, DRY SKIN
              <ul>
                <li class="endocrine">Hypothyroidism</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>NEED FOR MANUAL MANEUVERS (e.g., splinting)
              <ul>
                <li class="git cns">Pelvic floor dysfunction</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Along with the constipation, have you experienced
          anything else like pain, blood, or weight changes?"</span></div>
      <!-- P: Progression -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Progression</span>
          <ul>
            <li>PROGRESSIVELY WORSENING
              <ul>
                <li class="oncology git">Suggests an organic cause, e.g.,
                  growing obstruction/tumor</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Over the last few months, would you say the
          constipation has been getting worse?"</span></div>
      <!-- P: Pattern -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Pattern</span>
          <ul>
            <li>ALTERNATING WITH DIARRHEA
              <ul>
                <li class="git">IBS-M (Mixed type)</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>CHRONIC &amp; PERSISTENT
              <ul>
                <li class="git">Functional / Slow-transit constipation</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Is it a constant problem, or does it alternate
          with periods of normal bowel movements or diarrhea?"</span></div>
      <!-- E: Effect on life -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>: Effect on Life</span>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"How has this been impacting your daily life,
          comfort, and well-being?"</span></div>
      <!-- R: Red Flags -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Red Flags</span>
          <ul>
            <li>NEW ONSET &gt; 50 YEARS
              <ul>
                <li class="oncology git">Increased risk of colorectal cancer</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>UNEXPLAINED WEIGHT LOSS
              <ul>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>BLOOD IN STOOL
              <ul>
                <li class="oncology git emergency">Cancer, IBD, significant
                  bleed</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>SEVERE, PERSISTENT PAIN or VOMITING
              <ul>
                <li class="git emergency surgery">Bowel obstruction</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>IRON DEFICIENCY ANEMIA
              <ul>
                <li class="hematology oncology git">Suggests chronic GI blood
                  loss</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"I just need to ask some specific questions to make
          sure we're not missing anything serious."</span></div>
      <!-- S: Scale -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Severity / Bother Scale</span>
          <ul>
            <li>what is baseline?</li>
            <li>just stools</li>
            <li>no gas</li>
            <li>hard stools</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10, how much does this
          constipation bother you?"</span></div>
    </div>
    <script src="theme-toggle.js"></script>
    <script src="Iframe_height_mothership.js"></script>
    <script src="Iframe_height.js"></script>
    <script src="double_click_collapse_details.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
